What a year friends! 
2022 was a lot of things. Some were great, others, not so much. But we are definitely stronger and so much wiser from it all. 
So thankful for all your love and support, for my family, friends, amazing brides, clients and outstanding team for holding it down! 

Cheers to you- May the new year bring you an abundance of amazing opportunities, beautiful moments, and joyful experiences. 
Let’s welcome the new year full of things that have never been. We have before us a brand new book containing 365 blank pages. The book is called Opportunity and it’s first chapter is New Year’s Day.

Let’s start 2023 with a bang, the best is yet to come! 

Love you all, 
Happy New Year! 🥳

1/2 way to 𝒪𝒩𝐸!

What you see in this video is a short but treacherous journey full of lessons, love, hope, faith and determination. 

Most people know our family was thrown a curve ball when our baby Luna was diagnosed with a rare congenital heart disease. We’ve been very private about details, mostly because while she was going through the first surgery and recuperation, it was just too difficult for us to share or talk about. We finally got through the first surgery and are nearing the second phase of her care which includes a second open heart surgery and we could not be more proud of how wonderful she’s doing. 

Luna is your typical 6 month old, if you didn’t know her story, you would never know anything was going on. She is a sassy little warrior Princess who is strong, resilient, brave and totally meeting all milestones. While she loves mommy and daddy’s hugs and kisses, hands down her favorite person is her older brother. 

As we get ready for her next surgery and second wave of prayer request, it’s only fair we share a little more of her journey so far. A Journey we would do a million times over! 

Thank you for all your continued prayers and love for our Luna, it means the world to us!
#GODISINCONTROL 🙏

Our 🌙 is  𝒪 𝓃 𝑒 …..

Is she going to breathe on her own once she’s out? Will they let me see her? Can I hold her for just a second? Can they hold off lifeflight for a little while or are they going to transfer her right away? 
Will they wait for me to get discharged for her surgery? Can they even do that? Could you please just hold on for me? 
So many horrible thoughts crossed my mind on the way to the hospital, all the horrible thoughts I had suppressed since her diagnosis. 
I remember looking up at those bright lights in the OR and letting go, saying over and over in my head- God, you’re in control. It was like a trance, not just repeating that over and over but feeling it all over my body. Nothing shifted that thought until I heard your strong cry. The emotional tears filled with uncertainties were replaced with tears of joy and I knew in that very moment we were in for the ride of our lives, that we needed to buckle up but that you would be ok. 

We’ve slept in hospital chairs for months, skipped meals, cried from fear and joy. We advocated for you relentlessly and have become experts on your condition. 
We cried, You fought.
We wondered, You proved.
We prayed, You overcame.

My beautiful daughter, your fight is not over yet, but you have the heart of a warrior and you were designed to survive!

Happy 1st Birthday my sweet girl! 🎀

📷 @cocomichele_

The weight of Luna’s complex CHD diagnosis brought with it a heavy cloud of potential delays and the unsettling statistics about ASD among CHD babies. Processing this layered diagnosis felt like navigating a storm, adding a heap of worries onto our already burdened hearts.

Post her second open heart surgery this past April, Luna’s evaluation acknowledged the expected delays, a result of prolonged hospital stays between surgeries and procedures. Yet, Luna didn’t qualify for any OT or PT.
It was fuel to our fire and along with @msrachelforlittles here we are now. 

At just 16 months, Luna shines like a little marvel. She surpasses every milestone with a sparkle that fills my heart with pride. Her repertoire boasts over 15 words, and she effortlessly responds to commands, sharing her toys and food, gives kisses, and high-fiving with joy. She loves to sing, She started counting and recognizing shapes and colors in her charming, unique way. Luna’s a mimic extraordinaire, echoing every word she hears, including the occasional ones we wish she hadn’t picked up.

This journey hasn’t been an easy stroll in the park; it’s tested us in ways we never imagined. Mentally, emotionally, and physically, it’s been a mountain to climb. But you know what? I wouldn’t change a single moment of it.

Why? Because Luna, against all odds, is not just thriving—she’s defining what it means to live her best life. She’s our little WILD warrior, and witnessing her conquer every challenge is a feeling beyond words.
God is so good! 🙏

Our Bride Lisa looked absolutely flawless. The essence of bridal makeup lies in its ability to enhance your natural features rather than transform you.

In a beautiful twist of fate orchestrated by a higher power, just a few weeks after Bry booked me for her wedding, she reached out. Unfortunately, my response was delayed by a few days due to Luna’s hospital stay in late January last year. Little did I know, not only was she working in the Cardiac Intensive Care Unit, but she also happened to be one of the incredible nurses who cared for Luna. Beyond being a stunning bride, she is an exceptional nurse – a kindred spirit who supported us through some of the toughest days during Luna’s hospitalization.
